  "prompt": "What should I put on sweet potato fries?",
  "response": "Sweet potato fries are versatile and can be topped with a variety of ingredients to suit your taste. Here are some delicious ideas:\n\n### Savory Toppings:\n1. **Seasoning Blends**: Sprinkle with smoked paprika, garlic powder, cumin, chili powder, or Cajun seasoning.\n2. **Cheese**: Melted cheddar, feta, or parmesan cheese.\n3. **Herbs**: Fresh cilantro, parsley, or dill.\n4. **Creamy Dips**: Ranch, garlic aioli, chipotle mayo, or tzatziki.\n5. **Spicy Kick**: Hot sauce, sriracha, or a drizzle of buffalo sauce.\n6. **Nuts and Seeds**: Crumbled almonds, pecans, or toasted sesame seeds for crunch.\n\n### Sweet Toppings:\n1. **Cinnamon Sugar**: A mix of cinnamon and sugar for a sweet treat.\n2. **Honey or Maple Syrup**: Drizzle for a touch of sweetness.\n3. **Marshmallows**: Mini marshmallows melted on top (great for a dessert version).\n4. **Nut Butter**: Drizzle with almond butter, peanut butter, or tahini.\n\n### Combo Toppings:\n1. **Sweet and Spicy**: A mix of honey and chili flakes or hot sauce.\n2. **Rosemary and Parmesan**: Fresh rosemary and grated parmesan cheese.\n3. **Taco-Style**: Salsa, guacamole, and a dollop of sour cream.\n\n### Healthy Additions:\n1. **Avocado**: Sliced or mashed avocado on top.\n2. **Greek Yogurt**: A dollop of plain Greek yogurt with a sprinkle of herbs.\n3. **Kale Chips**: Crumbled kale chips for a crunchy, healthy twist.\n\nFeel free to mix and match based on your preferences!",
